step1.para:
Install the four bolts with lockwashers and tighten to 70 to 80 ft-lbs. (95 to 108 N·m)
                for aluminum clutch housings or 80 to 100 ft-lbs. (108 to 136 N·m) for cast iron clutch housings (
                Figure 246).

Install the six nuts with washers and tighten to 140 to 150 ft-lbs. (190 to 203 N·m)
                for aluminum clutch housings or 180 to 200 ft-lbs. (244 to 271 N·m) for cast iron clutch housings (
                Figure 247).
